<subSubSection id="56A095DAFF82FFD63EAFCFFFFC3A6ACB" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="53" pageId="3" pageNumber="52" type="description">
<paragraph id="1E05C651FF82FFD13EAFCFFFFD826A57" blockId="3.[151,1436,267,835]" pageId="3" pageNumber="52">
<emphasis id="2CCE1A43FF82FFD13EAFCFFFFEAB6A6E" bold="true" box="[198,350,499,525]" pageId="3" pageNumber="52">Description.</emphasis>
Size (all apterous): males, length 4.0–4.8 (
<typeStatus id="C10178F3FF82FFD13D30CFF8FC306A6D" box="[857,965,500,526]" pageId="3" pageNumber="52">holotype</typeStatus>
: 4.5), width 1.40–1.56 (
<typeStatus id="C10178F3FF82FFD13AB6CFF8FABE6A6D" box="[1247,1355,500,526]" pageId="3" pageNumber="52">holotype</typeStatus>
: 1.56); female (
<typeStatus id="C10178F3FF82FFD13E9FCC16FEAF6A57" box="[246,346,538,564]" pageId="3" pageNumber="52">allotype</typeStatus>
), length 4.8, width 1.83.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1E05C651FF82FFD13EAFCC4CFD946B20" blockId="3.[151,1436,267,835]" pageId="3" pageNumber="52">
<emphasis id="2CCE1A43FF82FFD13EAFCC4CFED76A39" bold="true" box="[198,290,576,602]" pageId="3" pageNumber="52">Colour.</emphasis>
Apterous form, body mainly yellowish brown, with faint brownish markings on dorsum (brown markings paler in female); head with median light stripe; pronotum and mesonotum with distinct median light stripe, marginated with light brown markings; lateral sides and submedian part with expanded faint brownish markings; brown lateral stripe on mesonotum, about 3/5 of length, running from anterior margin; metanotum dark brown, covered with golden pubescence; terga 1 and 2 and connexival margins dark brown; dorsum of abdomen with scattered golden pubescence; silvery spots as typical for genus (on mesoacetabula and metaacetabula). Venter light yellowish.
</paragraph>
<caption id="4AC596D9FF82FFD13EFEC9B8FA6D6F8D" pageId="3" pageNumber="52" startId="3.[151,271,1972,1996]" targetBox="[247,1326,902,1932]" targetPageId="3">
<paragraph id="1E05C651FF82FFD13EFEC9B8FA6D6F8D" blockId="3.[151,1436,1972,2030]" pageId="3" pageNumber="52">
<emphasis id="2CCE1A43FF82FFD13EFEC9B8FEB36FAF" bold="true" box="[151,326,1972,1996]" pageId="3" pageNumber="52">FIGURES 1–6.</emphasis>
Morphological features of 
<taxonomicName id="D9BABDD2FF82FFD13C1CC9B9FCAB6FAF" authorityName="Tran &amp; J. Polhemus" authorityYear="2009" box="[629,862,1973,1996]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Amemboides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="falcatus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="2CCE1A43FF82FFD13C1CC9B9FCAB6FAF" box="[629,862,1973,1996]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="52">Amemboides falcatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis id="2CCE1A43FF82FFD13D07C9B8FC336FAF" bold="true" box="[878,966,1972,1996]" pageId="3" pageNumber="52">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="37FDA738FF82FFD13D07C9B8FC336FAF" box="[878,966,1972,1996]" pageId="3" pageNumber="52" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
: (1) right front leg of male; (2) abdominal apex of male; (3) genital capsule, lateral view; (4) pygophore, ventral view; (5) left paramere; (6) proctiger, dorsal view.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="1E05C651FF85FFD63EAFCE94FDEA6984" blockId="4.[151,1436,152,1183]" pageId="4" pageNumber="53">
Apterous male: Head width 0.92, interocular width 0.51, eye length 0.42. Lengths of antennal segments 1–4: 1.03: 0.98: 1.14: 1.51. Pronotum length: 0.60, mesonotum length: 1.27. Mesosternum length: 1.57, metasternum length: 0.32. Lengths of leg segments (femur: tibia: tarsus 1: tarsus 2): front leg: 1.74: 1.56: 0.13: 0.29; middle leg: 3.77: 2.54: 0.56: 0.43; hind leg: 3.19: 1.56: 0.32: 0.37. Pregenital abdomen length 0.59. Genital segments relatively long: abdominal segment 8: dorsal length: 0.54, ventral length: 0.54, on ventral view, slightly longer than all preceding abdominal sterna combined (
<figureCitation id="8681DAD4FF85FFD63A6ACF55FBA66910" box="[1027,1107,345,371]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="3.[151,271,1972,1996]" captionTargetBox="[247,1326,902,1932]" captionTargetId="figure-266@3.[234,1352,893,1947]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Morphological features of Amemboides falcatus, sp. nov.: (1) right front leg of male; (2) abdominal apex of male; (3) genital capsule, lateral view; (4) pygophore, ventral view; (5) left paramere; (6) proctiger, dorsal view." pageId="4" pageNumber="53">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
). Pygophore with slightly emarginated hind margin, minus process next to the base of paramere (
<figureCitation id="8681DAD4FF85FFD63D9DCF8CFB9E69F9" box="[1012,1131,384,410]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="3.[151,271,1972,1996]" captionTargetBox="[247,1326,902,1932]" captionTargetId="figure-266@3.[234,1352,893,1947]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Morphological features of Amemboides falcatus, sp. nov.: (1) right front leg of male; (2) abdominal apex of male; (3) genital capsule, lateral view; (4) pygophore, ventral view; (5) left paramere; (6) proctiger, dorsal view." pageId="4" pageNumber="53">Figs. 3, 4</figureCitation>
). Proctiger long, slender, slightly constricted at middle part (
<figureCitation id="8681DAD4FF85FFD63C28CFAAFD7E69A3" box="[577,651,422,448]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="3.[151,271,1972,1996]" captionTargetBox="[247,1326,902,1932]" captionTargetId="figure-266@3.[234,1352,893,1947]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Morphological features of Amemboides falcatus, sp. nov.: (1) right front leg of male; (2) abdominal apex of male; (3) genital capsule, lateral view; (4) pygophore, ventral view; (5) left paramere; (6) proctiger, dorsal view." pageId="4" pageNumber="53">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
). Paramere long, falcate, with long scattered hairs, curved at 1/3 distal part, rounded apex (
<figureCitation id="8681DAD4FF85FFD63FA1CFC1FDE56984" box="[456,528,461,487]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="3.[151,271,1972,1996]" captionTargetBox="[247,1326,902,1932]" captionTargetId="figure-266@3.[234,1352,893,1947]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Morphological features of Amemboides falcatus, sp. nov.: (1) right front leg of male; (2) abdominal apex of male; (3) genital capsule, lateral view; (4) pygophore, ventral view; (5) left paramere; (6) proctiger, dorsal view." pageId="4" pageNumber="53">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1E05C651FF85FFD63EAFCFF8FC3A6ACB" blockId="4.[151,1436,152,1183]" pageId="4" pageNumber="53">Apterous female: Head width 0.98, interocular width 0.56, eye length 0.41. Lengths of antennal segments 1–4: 1.11: 0.98: 1.21: 1.35. Pronotum length: 0.57, mesonotum length: 1.71. Mesosternum length: 2.01, metasternum length: 0.44. Lengths of leg segments: front leg: 1.72: 1.59: 0.14: 0.33; middle leg: 4.21: 2.81: 0.60: 0.46; hind leg: 3.33: 1.74: 0.33: 0.40. Pregenital abdomen length: 1.16, sternite 7 length: 0.46, abdomen straight, sternite 7 not slanted downwards, connexival angles rounded.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="56A095DAFF85FFD63EACCCB9FB9D6AAC" box="[197,1128,693,719]" pageId="4" pageNumber="53" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="1E05C651FF85FFD63EACCCB9FB9D6AAC" blockId="4.[151,1436,152,1183]" box="[197,1128,693,719]" pageId="4" pageNumber="53">
<emphasis id="2CCE1A43FF85FFD63EACCCB9FEA46AAC" bold="true" box="[197,337,693,719]" pageId="4" pageNumber="53">Etymology.</emphasis>
This species is named after the falcate shape of the male paramere.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="56A095DAFF85FFD63EACCCD7FBE56C1B" pageId="4" pageNumber="53" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="1E05C651FF85FFD63EACCCD7FBE56C1B" blockId="4.[151,1436,152,1183]" pageId="4" pageNumber="53">
<emphasis id="2CCE1A43FF85FFD63EACCCD7FECA6A96" bold="true" box="[197,319,731,757]" pageId="4" pageNumber="53">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="D9BABDD2FF85FFD63F21CCD0FDB36A96" authorityName="Tran &amp; J. Polhemus" authorityYear="2009" box="[328,582,732,757]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Amemboides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="falcatus">
<emphasis id="2CCE1A43FF85FFD63F21CCD0FDB36A96" box="[328,582,732,757]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="53">Amemboides falcatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is closely related to 
<taxonomicName id="D9BABDD2FF85FFD63D2BCCD0FADF6A95" authority="Polhemus &amp; Andersen, 1984" authorityName="Polhemus &amp; Andersen" authorityYear="1984" box="[834,1322,732,758]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Amemboides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sexualis">
<emphasis id="2CCE1A43FF85FFD63D2BCCD0FC316A96" box="[834,964,732,757]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="53">A. sexualis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="7A2BBBA0FF85FFD63DA5CCD0FADF6A95" author="Polhemus &amp; Andersen" box="[972,1322,732,758]" firstAuthor="Polhemus" pageId="4" pageNumber="53" pagination="65 - 111" refId="ref4717" refString="Polhemus, J. T. &amp; Andersen, N. M. (1984) A revision of Amemboa Esaki with notes on the phylogeny and ecological evolution of eotrechine water striders (Insecta, Hemiptera, Gerridae). Steenstrupia, 10 (3), 65 - 111." type="journal article" year="1984">Polhemus &amp; Andersen, 1984</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. It shares with the latter species the following characteristics: falcate paramere, slender and constricted proctiger, apically emarginated pygophore, rounded connexival angles in female. However, it can be separated from 
<taxonomicName id="D9BABDD2FF85FFD63BEACD25FF036B0A" authorityName="Polhemus &amp; Andersen" authorityYear="1984" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Amemboides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sexualis">
<emphasis id="2CCE1A43FF85FFD63BEACD25FF036B0A" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="53">A. sexualis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by shorter genital segments (very long in 
<taxonomicName id="D9BABDD2FF85FFD63C8BCD5CFC956B0A" authorityName="Polhemus &amp; Andersen" authorityYear="1984" box="[738,864,848,873]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Amemboides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sexualis">
<emphasis id="2CCE1A43FF85FFD63C8BCD5CFC956B0A" box="[738,864,848,873]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="53">A. sexualis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), paramere curved at distal ⅓ (curved at distal ½ in 
<taxonomicName id="D9BABDD2FF85FFD63EDFCD7BFEC36BF3" authorityName="Polhemus &amp; Andersen" authorityYear="1984" box="[182,310,887,912]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Amemboides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sexualis">
<emphasis id="2CCE1A43FF85FFD63EDFCD7BFEC36BF3" box="[182,310,887,912]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="53">A. sexualis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), pygophore only slightly emarginated, not distinctly bifid apically and without long hair tufts laterally, female hind femur without long hairs basally, female sternite 7 not slanted downwards. Females of 
<taxonomicName id="D9BABDD2FF85FFD63EFECDC8FEED6BBE" authorityName="Tran &amp; J. Polhemus" authorityYear="2009" box="[151,280,964,989]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Amemboides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="falcatus">
<emphasis id="2CCE1A43FF85FFD63EFECDC8FEED6BBE" box="[151,280,964,989]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="53">A. falcatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
show an intermediate combination of characters between the two subspecies 
<taxonomicName id="D9BABDD2FF85FFD63AA5CDC8FA696BBE" authority="velaris" authorityName="velaris (Polhemus &amp; Andersen" authorityYear="1984" baseAuthorityName="velaris (Polhemus &amp; Andersen" baseAuthorityYear="1984" box="[1228,1436,964,989]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Amemboides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="velaris" subSpecies="velaris">
<emphasis id="2CCE1A43FF85FFD63AA5CDC8FA696BBE" box="[1228,1436,964,989]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="53">A. velaris velaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(sensu 
<bibRefCitation id="7A2BBBA0FF85FFD63E87CDE6FDA76C67" author="Polhemus &amp; Andersen" box="[238,594,1002,1028]" firstAuthor="Polhemus" pageId="4" pageNumber="53" pagination="65 - 111" refId="ref4717" refString="Polhemus, J. T. &amp; Andersen, N. M. (1984) A revision of Amemboa Esaki with notes on the phylogeny and ecological evolution of eotrechine water striders (Insecta, Hemiptera, Gerridae). Steenstrupia, 10 (3), 65 - 111." type="journal article" year="1984">Polhemus &amp; Andersen, 1984</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<taxonomicName id="D9BABDD2FF85FFD63CF1CDE6FC796C60" baseAuthorityName="Zettel &amp; Chen" baseAuthorityYear="1997" box="[664,908,1002,1027]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Amemboides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="velaris" subSpecies="orientalis">
<emphasis id="2CCE1A43FF85FFD63CF1CDE6FC796C60" box="[664,908,1002,1027]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="53">A. velaris orientalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(sensu 
<bibRefCitation id="7A2BBBA0FF85FFD63D84CDE6FB056C67" author="Zettel &amp; Chen" box="[1005,1264,1002,1028]" firstAuthor="Zettel" pageId="4" pageNumber="53" pagination="93 - 101" refId="ref4805" refString="Zettel, H. &amp; Chen, P. P. (1997) Three new taxa of Amemboa Esaki, 1925, from Thailand and Viet Nam (Heteroptera: Gerridae). Annales Historico-Naturales Musei Nationalis Hungarici, 89, 93 - 101." type="journal article" year="1997">Zettel &amp; Chen, 1997</bibRefCitation>
): the shape of abdominal segment 7 is similar to that of 
<taxonomicName id="D9BABDD2FF85FFD63C17CA1DFC926C49" baseAuthorityName="Zettel &amp; Chen" baseAuthorityYear="1997" box="[638,871,1041,1066]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Amemboides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="velaris" subSpecies="orientalis">
<emphasis id="2CCE1A43FF85FFD63C17CA1DFC926C49" box="[638,871,1041,1066]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="53">A. velaris orientalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but the short and sparse hairs on the connexival margin are as in 
<taxonomicName id="D9BABDD2FF85FFD63F30CA34FDD56C32" authority="velaris" authorityName="velaris (Polhemus &amp; Andersen" authorityYear="1984" baseAuthorityName="velaris (Polhemus &amp; Andersen" baseAuthorityYear="1984" box="[345,544,1080,1105]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Amemboides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="velaris" subSpecies="velaris">
<emphasis id="2CCE1A43FF85FFD63F30CA34FDD56C32" box="[345,544,1080,1105]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="53">A. velaris velaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; the absence of long black hairs on hind margins of terga 5–7 is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="D9BABDD2FF85FFD63BE3CA34FEAB6C1B" baseAuthorityName="Zettel &amp; Chen" baseAuthorityYear="1997" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Amemboides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="velaris" subSpecies="orientalis">
<emphasis id="2CCE1A43FF85FFD63BE3CA34FEAB6C1B" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="53">A velaris orientalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(whereas these structures are present in 
<taxonomicName id="D9BABDD2FF85FFD63D51CA53FBF56C1B" authority="velaris" authorityName="velaris (Polhemus &amp; Andersen" authorityYear="1984" baseAuthorityName="velaris (Polhemus &amp; Andersen" baseAuthorityYear="1984" box="[824,1024,1119,1144]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Amemboides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="velaris" subSpecies="velaris">
<emphasis id="2CCE1A43FF85FFD63D51CA53FBF56C1B" box="[824,1024,1119,1144]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="53">A. velaris velaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="56A095DAFF85FFD63EAFCA89FDA46CFC" box="[198,593,1157,1183]" pageId="4" pageNumber="53" type="distribution">
